<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="glial_types_DIGT1"><title>Tutor</title><page id="page_0"><question id="glial_types_DIGT1_0"><body>All four of the central nervous system glial cells protect the neurons in one way or another. Which pair of them is involved in the protecting by maintaining chemical barriers and fluid balance?</body><multiple_choice id="qsub_0" shuffle="true"><choice value="A">astrocytes and microglia</choice><choice value="B">microglia and ependymal</choice><choice value="C">ependymal and astrocytes</choice><choice value="D">microglia and oligodendrocytes</choice><choice value="E">oligodendrocytes and astrocytes</choice></multiple_choice><part id="qpart_0"><skillref idref="glial_types_function_SKILL" /><skillref idref="glial_types_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Microglia are phagocytes.</feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Microglia are phagocytes.</feedback></response><response match="C" score="10"><feedback>Correct. Both create a barrier of sorts controlling what fluids and chemicals are able to reach the neurons in the tissue from the blood or cerebrospinal fluid.</feedback></response><response match="D" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Microglia are phagocytes and oligodendrocytes produce myelin.</feedback></response><response match="E" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Oligodendrocytes produce myelin.</feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
